context:
여신전문금융업법 제2조(정의) 이 법에서 사용하는 용어의 뜻은 다음과 같다. <개정 2010. 3. 12., 2012. 3. 21., 2015. 1. 20., 2015. 7. 31., 2016. 3. 29., 2018. 2. 21., 2025. 10. 1.> 
5. “신용카드가맹점”이란 다음 각 목의 자를 말한다.

가. 신용카드업자와의 계약에 따라 신용카드회원ㆍ직불카드회원 또는 선불카드소지자(이하 “신용카드회원등”이라 한다)에게 신용카드ㆍ직불(直拂)카드 또는 선불(先拂)카드(이하 “신용카드등”이라 한다)를 사용한 거래에 의하여 물품의 판매 또는 용역의 제공 등을 하는 자

나. 신용카드업자와의 계약에 따라 신용카드회원등에게 물품의 판매 또는 용역의 제공 등을 하는 자를 위하여 신용카드등에 의한 거래를 대행(代行)하는 자(이하 “결제대행업체”라 한다)

여신전문금융업법 제20조(매출채권의 양도금지 등) ① 신용카드가맹점은 신용카드에 따른 거래로 생긴 채권(신용카드업자에게 가지는 매출채권을 포함한다. 이하 이 항에서 같다)을 신용카드업자와 「은행법」에 따라 설립된 은행(「중소기업은행법」에 따라 설립된 중소기업은행과 「농업협동조합법」에 따라 설립된 농협은행을 포함한다. 이하 이 조에서 같다) 외의 자(이하 이 조에서 “신용카드업자등 외의 자”라 한다)에게 양도하여서는 아니 되고, 신용카드업자등 외의 자는 이를 양수하여서는 아니 된다. 다만, 신용카드가맹점이 신용카드업자에게 가지는 매출채권을 「자산유동화에 관한 법률」 제2조제1호에 따른 자산유동화를 위하여 양도하는 경우에는 신용카드가맹점은 신용카드에 따른 거래로 생긴 채권을 신용카드업자등 외의 자에게 양도할 수 있고, 신용카드업자등 외의 자도 이를 양수할 수 있다. <개정 2010. 3. 12., 2016. 3. 29.>
The Interbank Savings Banks Act  Article 13 (Loan Review Committee, etc.)  (1) A savings bank (only a savings bank that meets the standards prescribed by Presidential Decree, taking into account its asset size, etc.) shall establish and operate a loan review committee and a department in charge of supervision over the review and post-loan management of loans in order to secure the soundness of loans, etc.
  (2) Matters necessary for the composition and operation of the loan review committee and the supervision department under paragraph (1), etc. shall be prescribed by Presidential Decree.
  [This Article Newly Inserted on Aug. 13, 2013]

The Interbank Savings Banks Act  Article 11 (Business) (1) A savings bank may conduct the following business in an organized and continuous manner for the purpose of profit: Provided, That a savings bank that meets the standards prescribed by Presidential Decree, taking into account its asset size, etc. shall not conduct the business under subparagraph 15: <Amended on Aug. 13, 2013>

1. Credit association business;

2. Credit installment business;

3. Receiving deposits and installments;

4. Lending money;

5. Discounting bills;

6. Domestic and foreign exchange (內ㆍ外國換) business;

7. Protective deposit (保護預受) business;

8. Receiving and paying agency business;

9. Mediating, arranging, or acting as an agent for mergers and acquisitions of corporations;

10. Acting as an agent for the State, public organizations, and financial institutions;

11. Acting on behalf of or entrusted with business by the Interbank Savings Banks Central Association under Article 25;

12. Issuing, managing, and settling debit electronic payment instruments under the Electronic Financial Transactions Act (only where it jointly conducts the business of the Interbank Savings Banks Central Association under Article 25-2 (1) 9);

13. Issuing, managing, selling, and settling prepaid electronic payment instruments under the Electronic Financial Transactions Act (only where it jointly conducts the business of the Interbank Savings Banks Central Association under Article 25-2 (1) 10);

14. Investment intermediary business, investment brokerage business, and trust business for which it has obtained permission from the Financial Services Commission under the Financial Investment Services and Capital Markets Act;

15. Installment financing business under the Special Act on Credit Finance (only a savings bank that meets the requirements prescribed by Presidential Decree, such as financial soundness, for the protection of traders, etc.);

16. Other business incidental to the business under subparagraphs 1 through 15 or business necessary for achieving the purpose of Article 1, for which it has obtained approval from the Financial Services Commission.

  (2) When conducting the business under paragraph (1), the minimum ratio of the total amount of credit extended to the sum of credit extended to individuals and small and medium enterprises within the business area out of the total amount of credit extended, and other matters necessary for a savings bank to comply with shall be prescribed by Presidential Decree.

  (3) A savings bank shall, when conducting the business under paragraph (1), facilitate financial convenience for low-income earners and small and medium enterprises in accordance with this Act and orders under this Act.

  [This Article Wholly Amended on Mar. 22, 2010]

The Act on Corporate Governance of Financial Companies Article 29 (Prohibition on Concurrent Service, etc.) A compliance officer and a risk management officer shall perform their duties with the caution of a good manager and shall not be in charge of the following business: Provided, That the same shall not apply where the concurrent service is deemed not to impair the performance of internal control and risk management duties: <Amended on Apr. 18, 2017>


1. Business related to asset management;

2. Essential business directly related to the business for which a financial company has obtained a permit or registered (hereinafter referred to as “essential business“) and ancillary business thereof;

3. Concurrent business of a financial company;

4. Business of a subsidiary, etc. of a financial holding company (excluding cases where a risk management officer of a financial holding company is in charge of risk management business of a subsidiary, etc. thereof);

5. Other business prescribed by Presidential Decree, which may impair the performance of internal control and risk management duties or make it difficult to devote oneself to such duties.

The Act on Corporate Governance of Financial Companies Article 25 (Appointment, etc. of Compliance Officer) (1) A financial company (excluding an investment advisory business entity and an investment discretionary business entity prescribed by Presidential Decree, taking into account the size of assets, etc.) shall appoint at least one person (hereinafter referred to as “compliance officer“) who examines compliance with internal control standards and investigates violations of such standards, and the compliance officer may report the results of the investigation to an audit committee or an auditor if he or she deems it necessary.

  (2) A financial company shall appoint a compliance officer from among executive officers or persons in charge of business execution. Provided, That a financial company or a domestic branch of a foreign financial company prescribed by Presidential Decree, taking into account the size of assets, financial business it conducts, etc. may appoint a compliance officer from among employees who are not executive officers or persons in charge of business execution.

  (3) Where a financial company (excluding a domestic branch of a foreign financial company) intends to appoint or dismiss a compliance officer, it shall pass a resolution at a board of directors, and where it intends to dismiss a compliance officer, it shall pass a resolution with the consent of at least two-thirds of the total number of directors.

  (4) The term of office of a compliance officer shall be not less than two years.

  (5) A financial company shall not appoint a part-time worker or a fixed-term worker under the Periodic Part-Time Workers Employment Protection Act as a compliance officer in violation of the provisions of paragraph (2) 2.

  (6) A financial company shall prepare and operate a separate remuneration payment and evaluation standard for a compliance officer, which is not linked to the financial management performance of the company.

Act on Corporate Governance of Financial Companies Decree Article 24 (Prohibition on Concurrent Service, etc.) (1) The business referred to in Article 29 (2) of the Act means any of the following business:

1. Banking business under Article 27 of the Banking Act;

2. Business under the Capital Markets and Financial Investment Business Act that a financial investment business entity is conducting, which is classified by type of financial investment business under Article 47 (1) of the Enforcement Decree of the same Act;

3. Business related to insurance that an insurance company is handling under the Insurance Business Act, which is prescribed in any of the following subparagraphs:

  Provided, That the following shall not apply where a risk management officer is a person performing such business:

  (a) Business related to the development of insurance products;

  (b) Actuarial business (excluding cases where a risk management officer is a person performing such business);

  (c) Business related to recruitment and conclusion of insurance contracts;

  (d) Business related to underwriting insurance contracts;

  (e) Business related to management of insurance contracts;

  (f) Business related to payment of insurance money;

  (g) Business related to reinsurance;

  (h) Other business related to insurance prescribed by the Financial Services Commission;

4. Business of a savings bank under Article 11 of the Interbank Savings Banks Act;

5. Business of a credit finance company under Article 46 (1) of the Special Act on Credit Finance.

  (2) The business referred to in Article 29 (5) of the Act means business falling under any of the following subparagraphs: Provided, That where a financial company and a domestic branch of a foreign financial company with total assets of less than 700 billion won (limited to cases where it does not concurrently conduct investment brokerage business for derivatives under Article 3 (2) 2 of the Capital Markets and Financial Investment Business Act), as prescribed in Article 20 (2), the business falling under any of the following subparagraphs may be concurrently conducted: <Amended on Sep. 5, 2017>

1. Risk management officer: Internal control-related business of a compliance officer under Article 25 (1) of the Act;

2. Compliance officer: Risk examination and management business of a risk management officer under Article 28 (1) of the Act.
형법 제329조(절도)  
타인의 재물을 절취한 자는 6년 이하의 징역 또는 1천만원 이하의 벌금에 처한다.  

형사소송법 제215조(현행범체와 체포)  
①검사 또는 사법경찰관은 현행범인을 체포하는 경우 피의자를 즉시 검사에게 인치(引致)하여야 하며, 검사는 10일 이내에 사건을 법원에 송치하거나 피의자를 석방하여야 한다.  
②체포한 현행범인을 인치할 때에는 체포의 요지와 이유, 변호인 선임권 및 변명의 기회를 주어야 한다.  

행정소송법 제18조(제소기간)  
①취소소송의 제소기간은 처분이 있음을 안 날부터 90일 이내로 한다. 다만, 행정심판청구를 할 수 있는 경우에는 재결을 거친 때는 재결서정본을 받은 날부터, 재결을 거치지 아니한 때는 처분이 있음을 안 날부터 각각 90일 이내로 한다.  

민법 제563조(매매의 의의)  
매매는 당사자 한쪽이 재산권을 상대방에게 이전할 것을 약정하고 상대방이 그 대금을 지급할 것을 약정함으로써 효력이 생긴다.  

헌법 제36조(혼인과 가족생활 등)  
①혼인과 가족생활은 개인의 존엄과 양성의 평등을 기초로 성립되고 유지되어야 한다.  
②국가는 모성의 보호를 위하여 노력하여야 하며, 특히 산모와 영유아를 위한 보호와 지원을 하여야 한다.

민법 제2조(신의성실)  
① 권리의 행사와 의무의 이행은 신의에 좇아 성실히 하여야 한다.  
② 권리는 남용하지 못한다.  

형법 제250조(살인)  
① 사람을 살해한 자는 사형, 무기 또는 5년 이상의 징역에 처한다.  

행정법 제12조(행정상 손해배상)  
① 행정안전부장관은 직무행위로 인하여 타인에게 손해를 입힌 경우에 그 손해를 배상하여야 한다.  

헌법 제10조(인간의 존엄과 행복추구권)  
① 모든 국민은 인간으로서의 존엄과 가치를 가지며, 행복을 추구할 권리를 가진다.  
② 국가는 개인이 가지는 불가침의 기본적 인권을 확인하고 이를 보장할 의무를 진다.
자본시장과 금융투자업에 관한 법률 시행령 제11조(증권의 모집ㆍ매출) ① 법 제9조제7항 및 제9항에 따라 50인을 산출하는 경우에는 청약의 권유를 하는 날 이전 6개월 이내에 해당 증권과 같은 종류의 증권에 대하여 모집이나 매출에 의하지 아니하고 청약의 권유를 받은 자를 합산한다. 다만, 다음 각 호의 어느 하나에 해당하는 자는 합산 대상자에서 제외한다. <개정 2009. 10. 1., 2010. 12. 7., 2013. 6. 21., 2013. 8. 27., 2016. 6. 28., 2016. 7. 28.>
2. 다음 각 목의 어느 하나에 해당하는 연고자

가. 발행인의 최대주주[「금융회사의 지배구조에 관한 법률」 제2조제6호가목에 따른 최대주주를 말한다. 이 경우 “금융회사”는 “법인”으로 보고, “발행주식(출자지분을 포함한다. 이하 같다)”은 “발행주식”으로 본다. 이하 같다]와 발행주식 총수의 100분의 5 이상을 소유한 주주

나. 발행인의 임원(「상법」 제401조의2제1항 각 호의 자를 포함한다. 이하 이 호에서 같다) 및 「근로복지기본법」에 따른 우리사주조합원

다. 발행인의 계열회사와 그 임원

라. 발행인이 주권비상장법인(주권을 모집하거나 매출한 실적이 있는 법인은 제외한다)인 경우에는 그 주주

마. 외국 법령에 따라 설립된 외국 기업인 발행인이 종업원의 복지증진을 위한 주식매수제도 등에 따라 국내 계열회사의 임직원에게 해당 외국 기업의 주식을 매각하는 경우에는 그 국내 계열회사의 임직원

바. 발행인이 설립 중인 회사인 경우에는 그 발기인

사. 그 밖에 발행인의 재무상황이나 사업내용 등을 잘 알 수 있는 연고자로서 금융위원회가 정하여 고시하는 자
Act on Registration of Lending Business, etc. and Protection of Financial Users 9-7 (Standards for Protecting Users of Lending Business) (1) Any person who has registered with the Financial Services Commission as a lender or other person referred to in Article 2 (2) through (5) and has an asset size prescribed by Presidential Decree or greater shall establish basic procedures and standards (hereinafter referred to as “protection standards“) to be followed by their employees in performing their duties in order to comply with statutes and regulations and protect their counterparties in transactions. <Amended on Jan. 21, 2025; Oct. 1, 2025>

(2) A lender or other person who establishes protection standards pursuant to paragraph (1) shall appoint at least one person (hereinafter referred to as “protection monitor“) to inspect whether the protection standards are being observed and investigate and audit any violation of the protection standards. <Amended on Jan. 21, 2025>

(3) A lender or other person referred to in paragraph (1) shall obtain resolution by the board of directors to appoint a protection monitor.

(4) A protection monitor shall be a person who meets each of the following requirements, and if he/she fails to meet any of the requirements in subparagraph 2 or 3 after becoming a protection monitor, he/she shall lose his/her position: <Amended on Jan. 21, 2025; Oct. 1, 2025>

1. A person who has a career as any of the following:

(a) A person who has worked for at least 10 years at the Bank of Korea or an institution subject to examination under Article 38 of the Act on the Establishment, etc. of the Financial Services Commission (including a foreign financial institution equivalent thereto);

(b) A person who holds a master's degree or higher in the field of finance or law and has worked for at least five years in a position of researcher or assistant professor or higher at a research institute or university;

(c) A person who has a lawyer's qualification and has worked for at least five years in a position related to such qualification, cumulatively;

(d) A person who has worked for at least five years at the Ministry of Finance and Economy, the Financial Services Commission, the Financial Supervisory Service established under the Act on the Establishment, etc. of the Financial Services Commission (hereinafter referred to as the “Financial Supervisory Service“), or the Securities and Futures Commission under the same Act, and has been five years or more since he/she left or retired from such institution;

(e) Other persons prescribed by Presidential Decree for the protection of users of lending business.

2. A person who does not fall under any subparagraph of Article 4 (1);

3. A person who has no record of having been subject to a measure equivalent to or greater than a request for caution or warning by the Financial Services Commission or the head of the Financial Supervisory Service (hereinafter referred to as the “head of the Financial Supervisory Service“) for violating this Act, financial-related statutes and regulations, or other statutes and regulations related to financial businesses and transactions within the latest five years.

(5) The protection standards and other matters necessary for the protection monitor shall be prescribed by Presidential Decree.

[This Article Newly Inserted on Jul. 24, 2015]
[Paragraphs 1 through 4 Shall Apply from Jan. 2, 2026]

Act on the Establishment, etc. of the Financial Services Commission Article 38 (Examination Target Institutions) (1) The institutions subject to examination by the Financial Supervisory Service shall be as follows: <Amended on May 29, 2016>

1. Banks established by obtaining permission under the Banking Act;

2. Financial investment business entities, securities finance companies, merchant banking companies, and name change agencies under the Financial Investment Services and Capital Markets Act;

3. Insurance companies under the Insurance Business Act;

4. Mutual savings banks and their central associations under the Mutual Savings Banks Act;

5. Credit cooperatives and their central associations under the Credit Unions Act;

6. Specialized credit finance companies and concurrent credit finance business entities under the Special Act on Asset-Backed Securitization;

7. Nonghyup Bank under the Agricultural Cooperatives Act;

8. Shinhan Bank under the Fisheries Cooperatives Act;

9. Institutions prescribed by Presidential Decree as subject to examination by the Financial Supervisory Service in other statutes;

10. Other persons prescribed by Presidential Decree as engaging in financial businesses and financial-related businesses.

[This Article Wholly Amended on Mar. 21, 2012]

Asset-Backed Securitization Act Article 34 (Investigation) (1) The Financial Services Commission may order any of the following persons to submit reports or materials for reference or require the head of the Financial Supervisory Service to inspect books, documents, or other objects if there is any matter that violates this Act or orders or dispositions under this Act or if it is deemed necessary for the protection of investors or the maintenance of sound trading order:

1. A securitization company, etc.;

2. A person who has been entrusted with business or asset management by a securitization company, etc.;

3. A person who has sold or entrusted assets to a securitization company, etc.;

4. Other persons suspected of violating this Act.

(3) The provisions of Article 426 (2) and (4) of the Financial Investment Services and Capital Markets Act shall apply mutatis mutandis to investigations under paragraphs (1) and (2).

Financial Investment Services and Capital Markets Act Article 426 (Reports and Investigations)
(2) The Financial Services Commission may request the following matters from persons suspected of violating this Act or other related persons for the purpose of investigations under paragraph (1): Provided, That the same shall not apply to matters falling under subparagraph 3 where it is deemed necessary to protect the rights and interests of investors: <Amended on Feb. 29, 2008; May 28, 2013>

1. Submission of a statement of facts and circumstances related to the investigation;

2. Attendance for a statement related to the investigation;

3. Submission of books, documents, and other objects necessary for the investigation;
(4) The Financial Services Commission may request a financial investment business entity, a financial investment business-related institution, or a trading corporation to submit materials necessary for an investigation under paragraph (1) in accordance with the methods prescribed by Presidential Decree if it deems it necessary to conduct an investigation. <Amended on Feb. 29, 2008>

gold_answer:
{
  "step 1": "금융실명법 제4조 제1항은 ‘금융회사등에 종사하는 자는 명의인의 서면상의 요구나 동의를 받지 아니하고는 그 금융거래의 내용에 대한 정보 또는 자료(이하 “거래정보등”)를 타인에게 제공하거나 누설하여서는 아니 된다’고 규정하고 있다. 따라서 질문에서 묻는 “제공하거나 누설하여서는 아니되는 정보의 범위”는 바로 이 ‘거래정보등’의 의미에 해당한다.",
  "step 2": "‘거래정보등’의 구체적 의미는 같은 법률을 시행하는 시행령 제6조에 명시되어 있다. 시행령 제6조는 “법 제4조 제1항 및 이 영 제5조에 따른 금융거래의 내용에 대한 정보 또는 자료는 특정인의 금융거래사실과 금융회사등이 보유하고 있는 금융거래에 관한 기록의 원본·사본 및 그 기록으로부터 알게 된 것”이라고 규정한다.",
  "step 3": "또한 시행령 제6조는 위 범위에서 ‘금융거래사실을 포함한 금융거래의 내용이 누구의 것인지를 알 수 없는 것(당해 거래정보등만으로 그 거래자를 알 수 없더라도 다른 거래정보등과 용이하게 결합하여 그 거래자를 알 수 있는 것을 제외한다)’은 제외된다고 명시하고 있다. 이는 ‘거래정보등’의 제외 사유를 추가로 설명한다.",
  "step 4": "따라서, 금융실명법 제4조 제1항에 따라 명의인의 서면상의 요구·동의 없이 타인에게 제공하거나 누설해서는 안 되는 ‘거래정보등’은 **(1) 특정인의 금융거래사실, (2) 금융회사 등이 보유하고 있는 해당 거래에 관한 기록의 원본·사본, (3) 그 기록으로부터 알게 된 정보**를 포함한다. 단, **금융거래사실을 포함한 내용이 누구의 것인지를 알 수 없는 경우(당해 정보만으로는 거래자를 식별할 수 없으며, 다른 정보와 결합해도 식별이 불가능한 경우)는 제외**된다."
}

{
  "step 1": "‘실지명의’는 금융실명거래 및 비밀보장에 관한 법률 제2조제4호에 따라 정의되며, 시행령 제3조 제4호에 의하면 외국인의 경우 ‘출입국관리법’에 의한 등록외국인기록표에 기재된 성명 및 등록번호이며, 외국인등록증이 발급되지 않은 경우에는 여권 또는 신분증에 기재된 성명 및 번호라고 명시되어 있다.",
  "step 2": "따라서 외국인에게 기명식 선불전자지급수단을 발행하려면 실지명의로서 위 규정에 해당하는 ‘등록외국인기록표에 기재된 성명 및 등록번호’를 사용해야 하고, 외국인등록증이 없는 경우에는 여권 또는 기타 신분증에 기재된 성명 및 번호를 실지명의로 적용한다.",
  "step 3": "전자금융거래법 시행령 제13조 제1항제2호는 ‘금융실명거래 및 비밀보장에 관한 법률’ 제2조제4호에 따른 실지명의로 발행되는 선불전자지급수단에 대해 발행권면 최고한도를 200만원으로 설정하도록 규정하고 있다. 이는 실지명의 요건을 충족하는 경우 해당 한도 내에서 발행이 허용됨을 의미한다.",
  "step 4": "위 규정들만으로는 비거주자 외국인에 대한 추가적인 ‘외국환거래법’·‘특정 금융거래정보의 보고 및 이용에 관한 법률’ 등 다른 법령의 적용 여부를 판단할 근거가 없으므로, 해당 부분은 주어진 context만으로는 추론할 수 없다."
}

